During a White House press briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney responded to questions regarding the proposed legislation that would allow people to keep their health care coverage, even if it does not meet the requirements of the Affordable Care Act. Carney explained that the focus of the White House is on implementing the ACA and fixing the problems with the website. He emphasized that the ACA promises affordable, quality health care coverage for all Americans. Carney also addressed concerns about cancellation notices that some individuals have received. He stated that the White House is committed to providing information to those affected and ensuring that they understand their options. Carney acknowledged that there have been communication challenges and that the website issues have made it difficult for people to access information. However, he stressed that the goal is to provide better coverage and options for individuals.